Before non-trivial work, read **`ai-context.md`** (stack, structure, conventions, integrations, anti-patterns, env names).

For setup and deployment, use **`README.md`** and **`.env.example`**. For WordPress REST checks and troubleshooting, use **`docs/wordpress-connection-guide.md`**.

Keep changes minimal and aligned with patterns in `ai-context.md`. When you change conventions or add env vars, update **`ai-context.md`**, **`.env.example`**, and **`README.md`** as needed.
